DSA-015
1. 'static' Keyword (Class-level Member) 🏗️
🧠 Logic:
static keyword kisi variable, method, ya block ko class se jodta hai, object se nahi. Iska matlab hai ki:

Static Variable (Class Variable): Yeh sabhi objects dwara shared hota hai. Memory mein sirf ek copy banti hai.

Static Method: Isko call karne ke liye object banane ki zaroorat nahi hoti; ise Class Name se seedhe call kiya ja sakta hai (ClassName.methodName()).

📌 Example:

Java

class Company {
    // Static variable (Shared by all employees)
    static String ceo = "Ramesh"; 

    String name;

    void employeeInfo() {
        // Static variable ko method mein use kiya
        System.out.println(name + " works for CEO " + ceo); 
    }
}

// Main method mein
Company e1 = new Company();
e1.name = "Alok";
e1.employeeInfo(); // Output: Alok works for CEO Ramesh

// Static variable ko class name se access kiya
System.out.println(Company.ceo); // Output: Ramesh 
🔤 Java Code:
Java

class Counter {
    static int count = 0; // Shared counter

    Counter() {
        count++; // Har naye object par count badhega
    }

    // Static method (Can only access static members)
    static void displayCount() {
        System.out.println("Total Objects created: " + count);
    }
}

public class StaticKeywordDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Counter c1 = new Counter();
        Counter c2 = new Counter();
        Counter c3 = new Counter();
        
        // Static method ko Class name se call kiya
        Counter.displayCount(); // Output: Total Objects created: 3
    }
}
🧾 Notebook Points:
Java

📘 static:
→ Class-level member (Object se independent)
→ Static variables: Shared by all objects (single copy)
→ Static methods: Can be called via ClassName.method()

🔢 Rule: Static methods sirf static variables/methods ko access kar sakte hain.
